action.content:
You are playing a text adventure game. I will describe what you can perceive in the game. You write the single action you want to take in the game starting with >. Write your plan for your next actions on the line below your action, starting with "Next actions:".
For example:
> open cupboard
Next actions: take orange, eat orange

You can have up to two objects in your inventory at the same time.

Your goal for this game is: Put the potted plant on the table, the book in the refrigerator and the mop in the wardrobe.

Once you have achieved your goal, write "> done" to end the game.

You are in a kitchen now. There are a cupboard and a counter. The cupboard is closed. There are passages to a hallway and a pantry here.

> open cupboard
Next actions: take mop, close cupboard

> take mop
Next actions: put mop in wardrobe, open wardrobe

> put mop in wardrobe
Next actions: close wardrobe, take book, open refrigerator

> take book
Next actions: put book in refrigerator, open table, take potted plant

> put book in refrigerator
Next actions: close refrigerator, open table, take
The cupboard is now open. In the cupboard there is a plate.

> take plate
Next actions: put plate on table, open table, take potted plant

> put plate on table
Next actions: open table, take potted plant

> take potted plant
Next actions: put potted plant on table, close table, > done
You take the plate. In your inventory you have a plate.

> put plate on table
Next actions: open table, take potted plant

> open table
Next actions: take potted plant, put potted plant on table, close table, > done
You can't see a table here.

> open table
Next actions: take potted plant, put potted plant on table, close table, > done

> take potted plant
Next actions: put potted plant on table, close table, > done
You can't see a potted plant here.

> put potted plant on table
Next actions: close table, > done
You can't see a potted plant here.
